node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/02-guides/self-hosting.mdx:265:When using a CDN in front of your Next.js application, the page will include `Cache-Control: private` response header when dynamic APIs are accessed. This ensures that the resulting HTML page is marked as non-cacheable. If the page is fully prerendered to static, it will include `Cache-Control: public` to allow the page to be cached on the CDN.
